Definition: or נֵרִיָּהוּ; from {{h5216}} and {{h3050}}; light of Jah; Nerijah, an Israelite; Neriah.

or נָסָה; (Psalm 4:6 [7]), a primitive root; to lift, in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, absolute and relative; accept, advance, arise, (able to, (armor), suffer to) bear(-er, up), bring (forth), burn, carry (away), cast, contain, desire, ease, exact, exalt (self), extol, fetch, forgive, furnish, further, give, go on, help, high, hold up, honorable (  man), lade, lay, lift (self) up, lofty, marry, magnify, × needs, obtain, pardon, raise (up), receive, regard, respect, set (up), spare, stir up,   swear, take (away, up), × utterly, wear, yield.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5375}}; carry away, make insurrection, take.
a primitive root; to lead astray, i.e. (mentally) to delude, or (morally) to seduce; beguile, deceive, × greatly, × utterly.
of foreign origin; Nergal, a Cuthite deity; Nergal.
from {{h5370}} and {{h8272}}; Nergal-Sharetser, the name of two Babylonians; Nergal-sharezer.
from an unused root meaning to roll to pieces; a slanderer; talebearer, whisperer.
of foreign origin; nard, an aromatic; spikenard.
a primitive root (perhaps identical with {{h5377}}, through the idea of imposition); to lend on interest; by implication, to dun for debt; × debt, exact, giver of usury.
passive participle feminine of {{h5375}}; something taken, i.e. a present; gift.

a primitive root; to puff, in various applications (literally, to inflate, blow hard, scatter, kindle, expire; figuratively, to disesteem); blow, breath, give up, cause to lose (life), seething, snuff.
or נְפִל; from {{h5307}}; properly, a feller, i.e. a bully or tyrant; giant.
from {{h5301}}; a gust; Nophach, a place in Moab; Nophah.
from {{h5314}}; refreshed; Naphish, a son of Ishmael, and his posterity; Naphish.
plural from an unused root meaning to scatter; expansions; Nephisim, a Temple-servant; Nephusim (from the margin).

a primitive root; to fall, in a great variety of applications (intransitive or causative, literal or figurative); be accepted, cast (down, self, (lots), out), cease, die, divide (by lot), (let) fail, (cause to, let, make, ready to) fall (away, down, -en, -ing), fell(-ing), fugitive, have (inheritance), inferior, be judged (by mistake for {{h6419}}), lay (along), (cause to) lie down, light (down), be (× hast) lost, lying, overthrow, overwhelm, perish, present(-ed, -ing), (make to) rot, slay, smite out, × surely, throw down.
from an unused root meaning to glisten; shining; a gem, probably the garnet; emerald.
or נֵפֶל; from {{h5307}}; something fallen, i.e. an abortion; untimely birth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5307}}; fall (down), have occasion.
(Aramaic) irregular plural feminine of {{h606}}; women.
from {{h5382}}; oblivion; forgetfulness.
a primitive root; to reach (literally or figuratively); ability, be able, attain (unto), (be able to, can) get, lay at, put, reach, remove, wax rich, × surely, (over-) take (hold of, on, upon).
a primitive root; to blow; by implication, to disperse; (cause to) blow, drive away.

a primitive root (rather identical with {{h5382}}, in the sense of {{h5378}}); to lend or (by reciprocity) borrow on security or interest; creditor, exact, extortioner, lend, usurer, lend on (taker on) usury.
a primitive root; to forget; figuratively, to neglect; causatively, to remit, remove; forget, deprive, exact.
or rather, נְשֻׂאָה; feminine. passive participle of {{h5375}}; something borne, i.e. a load; carriage.
from {{h5382}}, in the sense of failure; rheumatic or crippled (from the incident to Jacob); which shrank.
or נָשִׂא; from {{h5375}}; properly, an exalted one, i.e. a king or sheik; also a rising mist; captain, chief, cloud, governor, prince, ruler, vapour.
from {{h5383}}; a debt; debt.
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to issue; causatively, to bring out; come (go, take) forth (out).
(Aramaic) from {{h5312}}; an outgo, i.e. expense; expense.
a primitive root; to dash to pieces, or scatter; be beaten in sunder, break (in pieces), broken, dash (in pieces), cause to be discharged, dispersed, be overspread, scatter.
from {{h5310}}; a storm (as dispersing); scattering.
for {{h5299}}; a height; country.
from {{h5130}} in the sense of shaking to pieces; a dripping i.e. of honey (from the comb); honeycomb.
a primitive root; to breathe; passively, to be breathed upon , i.e. (figuratively) refreshed (as if by a current of air); (be) refresh selves (-ed).

from {{h5314}}; properly, a breathing creature, i.e. animal of (abstractly) vitality; used very widely in a literal, accommodated or figurative sense (bodily or mental); any, appetite, beast, body, breath, creature, × dead(-ly), desire, × (dis-) contented, × fish, ghost,   greedy, he, heart(-y), (hath, × jeopardy of) life (× in jeopardy), lust, man, me, mind, mortally, one, own, person, pleasure, (her-, him-, my-, thy-) self, them (your) -selves,   slay, soul,   tablet, they, thing, (× she) will, × would have it.
from {{h6605}}; opened, i.e. a spring; Nephtoach, a place in Palestine; Neptoah.
from {{h6617}}; properly, wrestled; but used (in the plural) transitively, a struggle; wrestling.
a primitive root; to breeze, i.e. blow up fresh (as the wind); blow.
from {{h5398}}; properly, a breeze, i.e. (by implication) dusk (when the evening breeze prevails); dark, dawning of the day (morning), night, twilight.
from {{h5391}}; interest on a debt; usury.
for {{h3957}}; a cell; chamber.
from {{h5401}}; a kiss; kiss.
a primitive root; to strike with a sting (as a serpent); figuratively, to oppress with interest on a loan; bite, lend upon usury.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5397}}; vital breath; breath.
from {{h5395}}; a puff, i.e. wind, angry or vital breath, divine inspiration, intellect. or (concretely) an animal; blast, (that) breath(-eth), inspiration, soul, spirit.
a primitive root; to pluck off, i.e. divest, eject or drop; cast (out), drive, loose, put off (out), slip.
a primitive root; properly, to blow away, i.e. destroy; destroy.

a primitive root;	also as denominative from {{h5331}}; properly, to glitter from afar, i.e. to be eminent (as a superintendent, especially of the Temple services and its music); to be permanent; excel, chief musician (singer), oversee(-r), set forward.
feminine of {{h5322}}; a blossom; flower.

a primitive root; properly, to go forth, i.e. (by implication) to be expelled, and (consequently) desolate; causatively, to lay waste; also (specifically), to quarrel; be laid waste, runinous, strive (together).
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h5324}}; fixedness, i.e. firmness; strength.
passive participle of {{h5324}}; fixed, i.e. a handle; haft.

a primitive root; to station, in various applications (literally or figuratively); appointed, deputy, erect, establish, × Huzzah (by mistake for a proper name), lay, officer, pillar, present, rear up, set (over, up), settle, sharpen, establish, (make to) stand(-ing, still, up, upright), best state.
a primitive root; to go away; flee.
from {{h5340}}; a flower (from its brilliancy); also a hawk (from it flashing speed); blossom, hawk.
from {{h6617}}; my wrestling; Naphtali, a son of Jacob, with the tribe descended from him, and its territory; Naphtali.
plural of foreign origin,; Naphtuchim, an Egyptian tribe; Naptuhim.
a primitive root; to catch fire; burn, kindle.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5337}}; to extricate; deliver, rescue.
from {{h5322}}; a blossom; flower.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5329}}; to become chief; be preferred.

or נֵצַח; from {{h5329}}; properly, a goal, i.e. the bright object at a distance travelled towards; hence (figuratively), splendor, or (subjectively) truthfulness, or (objectively) confidence; but usually (adverbially), continually (i.e. to the most distant point of view); alway(-s), constantly, end, (  n-) ever(more), perpetual, strength, victory.
probably identical with {{h5331}}, through the idea of brilliancy of color; juice of the grape (as blood red); blood, strength.
or נְצִב; from {{h5324}}; something stationary, i.e. a prefect, a military post, a statue; garrison, officer, pillar.
the same as {{h5333}}; station; Netsib, a place in Palestine; Nezib.
from {{h5329}}; conspicuous; Netsiach, a Temple-servant; Neziah.
from {{h5341}}; properly, conservative; but used passively, delivered; preserved.

a primitive root; to snatch away, whether in a good or a bad sense; × at all, defend, deliver (self), escape, × without fail, part, pluck, preserve, recover, rescue, rid, save, spoil, strip, × surely, take (out).
active participle from the same as {{h5348}}; a spotter (of sheep or cattle), i.e. the owner or tender (who thus marks them); herdman, sheepmaster.
from an unused root meaning to mark (by puncturing or branding); spotted; speckled.
a bezel (for a gem); pipe.

a primitive root; to puncture, literally (to perforate, with more or less violence) or figuratively (to specify, designate, libel); appoint, blaspheme, bore, curse, express, with holes, name, pierce, strike through.
from {{h5344}}; female (from the sexual form); female.
the same as {{h5345}}; dell; Nekeb, a place in Palestine; Nekeb.

a primitive root; to guard, in a good sense (to protect, maintain, obey, etc.) or a bad one (to conceal, etc.); besieged, hidden thing, keep(-er, -ing), monument, observe, preserve(-r), subtil, watcher(-man).
a primitive root; to glare, i.e. be bright-colored; sparkle.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h5352}}; clean; pure.
from {{h5341}} in the sense of greenness as a striking color; a shoot; figuratively, a descendant; branch.
a primitive root; to grudge, i.e. avenge or punish; avenge(-r, self), punish, revenge (self), × surely, take vengeance.
from {{h5358}}; revenge; avenged, quarrel, vengeance.
or נִקָּיֹן; from {{h5352}}; clearness (literally or figuratively); cleanness, innocency.
from an unused root meaning to bore; a cleft; hole.
a primitive root; to loathe; weary.
or נָקִיא; (Joel 4:19; Jonah 1:14), from {{h5352}}; innocent; blameless, clean, clear, exempted, free, guiltless, innocent, quit.

a primitive root; to be (or make) clean (literally or figuratively); by implication (in an adverse sense) to be bare, i.e. extirpated; acquit × at all, × altogether, be blameless, cleanse, (be) clear(-ing), cut off, be desolate, be free, be (hold) guiltless, be (hold) innocent, × by no means, be quit, be (leave) unpunished, × utterly, × wholly.
feminine of {{h5348}} (in the figurative sense of marked); distinction; Nekoda, a Temple-servant; Nekoda.
from the same as {{h5348}}; a crumb (as broken to spots); also a biscuit (as pricked); cracknel, mouldy.
feminine of {{h5348}}; a boss; stud.
the same as {{h5216}}; lamp; Ner, an Israelite; Ner.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5367}}; used in the sense of {{h5362}}; to knock; smote.
from {{h5362}}; a threshing (of olives); shaking.

a primitive root; to strike with more or less violence (beat, fell, corrode); by implication (of attack) to knock together, i.e. surround or circulate; compass (about, -ing), cut down, destroy, go round (about), inclose, round.
a primitive root; to feel aversion; be alienated.
feminine of {{h5359}}; avengement, whether the act or the passion; avenge, revenge(-ing), vengeance.
a primitive root; to entrap (with a noose), literally or figuratively; catch (lay a) snare.
from {{h5365}}; a fissure; cleft, clift.
a primitive root; to bore (penetrate, quarry); dig, pick out, pierce, put (thrust) out.
from {{h5362}}; probably a rope (as encircling); rent.
